        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 3:41PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Drummond, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Drummond, New Chicago, and Hall.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 146 and 159.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
